# Picking Module

## Overview

Picking module is responsible for warehouse order collection before packing.

Workflow:

IMPORT → PICKING → PACKING → SHIPPING

Operator creates a picking batch which groups orders for the same carrier.

---

# API Endpoints

## Batch lifecycle

POST /api/v1/picking/batches/open

Creates new picking batch.

Body:

{
  "carrier_key": "dpd",
  "target_orders_count": 10
}

---

GET /api/v1/picking/batches/current

Returns currently open batch for operator.

---

GET /api/v1/picking/batches/{batchId}

Returns batch details.

---

POST /api/v1/picking/batches/{batchId}/refill

Adds additional orders if batch has less than target_orders_count.

---

POST /api/v1/picking/batches/{batchId}/close

Closes batch when all orders are picked or dropped.

---

POST /api/v1/picking/batches/{batchId}/abandon

Marks batch as abandoned.

---

# Picking operations

GET /api/v1/picking/batches/{batchId}/orders

Returns orders in batch.

---

GET /api/v1/picking/batches/{batchId}/products

Returns aggregated product list for batch.

---

POST /api/v1/picking/orders/{orderId}/items/{itemId}/picked

Marks item as picked.

---

POST /api/v1/picking/orders/{orderId}/items/{itemId}/missing

Marks item as missing.

Body:

{
  "reason": "missing on shelf"
}

---

POST /api/v1/picking/orders/{orderId}/drop

Drops order from batch.

Body:

{
  "reason": "manual"
}

